article.description: — Nic Lynch had a career-high 30 points as Lehigh topped American 78-61 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Lynch scores 30 to carry Lehigh past American 78-61
article.linkText: Lynch scores 30 to carry Lehigh past American 78-61
article.story: BETHLEHEM, Pa. -- — Nic Lynch had a career-high 30 points as Lehigh topped American 78-61 on Wednesday night. Keith Higgins Jr had 13 points for Lehigh (11-18, 9-8 Patriot League). Jeameril Wilson also had 13 points. Tyler Whitney-Sidney had 12 points. Lehigh totaled 46 first-half points, a season high for the team. Stacy Beckton Jr. had 17 points and six rebounds for the Eagles (8-21, 4-13). Colin Smalls added 16 points. The Mountain Hawks improve to 2-0 against the Eagles for the season. Lehigh defeated American 63-61 on Jan. 1. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
